Every project needs governance. OMSF requires that hosted projects have clear governance structures. More philosophically, every project has governance: plans are formed, decisions are made, actions are taken, software is developed. Governance is the answer to the questions of “who” and “how.”

Notably, this governance is different from a classical project management viewpoint of a governance that exists in other fields. Here, we refer to governance as the group of stakeholders who oversee the project and ensure operational excellence.

